Basic system utilities for Alchemy.

cat <file>...
  Print files on the output. If no files specified then
  data is read from standard input.

chmod <modifiers> <files>...
  Modify attributes on given files. Modifiers are: -r, +r,
  -w, +w, -x, +x.

cp <source> <destination>
cp <files>... <directory>
  Copy contents of one file to another or copy multiple files
  in given directory.

date
  Print current date and time on the output.

echo <messages>...
  Print given messages on the output.

env <key>=<value>... <command> <arguments>
  Run program in a changed environment.

install <files>... <directory>
  Copy files to the specified directory and set their
  attributes.

ls <directory>
  Print names of all files contained in given directory.
  If argument is not specified then list contents of the
  current working directory.

mkdir <directory>
  Make new empty directory in the file system.

mv <source> <destination>
mv <files>... <directory>
  Move/rename file or move multiple files in given directory.

rm <files>...
  Remove specified files.
